The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Cow slaughter burns mosque
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Cow slaughter burns mosque
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Shimla, Feb. 12: An angry mob today set on fire a mosque and a madrasah in Shimlas Nerwa area to protest the alleged slaughter of a cow.        
	More than 500 people gathered in Nerwa after news spread that a cow had been slaughtered in a nearby jungle on Thursday. A mosque and a madrasah has been damaged. One person has been arrested for cow slaughter, R.M. Sharma, the Shimla superintendent of police, said.        
	Around 200 Muslim families live in the area.         
	The district administration claimed the situation was under control.                                                                                                                                                          
